  "abstract": "We revisit the classic information extraction problem of document-level\ntemplate filling. We argue that sentence-level approaches are ill-suited to the\ntask and introduce a generative transformer-based encoder-decoder framework\nthat is designed to model context at the document level: it can make extraction\ndecisions across sentence boundaries; is \\emph{implicitly} aware of noun phrase\ncoreference structure, and has the capacity to respect cross-role dependencies\nin the template structure. We evaluate our approach on the MUC-4 dataset, and\nshow that our model performs substantially better than prior work. We also show\nthat our modeling choices contribute to model performance, e.g., by implicitly\ncapturing linguistic knowledge such as recognizing coreferent entity mentions.\nOur code for the evaluation script and models will be open-sourced at\nhttps://github.com/xinyadu/doc_event_entity for reproduction purposes.",
